Use MAUI's `#if` platform directives combined with the standard DI container in `CreateMauiApp()`:

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs
public static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()
{
    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();
    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();

#if ANDROID
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();
#elif IOS
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.iOSNotificationService>();
#elif WINDOWS
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();
#endif

    return builder.Build();
}
```

Each implementation lives under its respective `Platforms/` folder (which is already per-platform compiled by the SDK). This way only the relevant type is compiled and registered per target, so it never breaks on other platforms.

**Alternative:** If you prefer no `#if` directives, put each implementation directly in its platform folder (e.g., `Platforms/Android/NotificationService.cs`) using partial classes or a shared name, and rely on MAUI's per-platform folder compilation — then register a single concrete type that only exists in each platform's build.
